The '''Federation of [[European Union]] Manufacturers and Suppliers of Ingredients to the Bakery, Confectionery, and ''Patisserie'' Industries''' ({{lang-fr|Fédération des Industries de Matières Premières et Améliorants pour la Boulangerie et Confisserie dans la CEE}}) or '''FEDIMA''' is a [[Trade unions in Europe|European]] [[trade union]] within the [[baking industry]]. It was established 20 May 1969.<ref name="hist">Fedima. "[http://fedima.drupalgardens.com/content/history History]". Accessed 22 Jan 2013.</ref>
It is based in [[Brussels]], [[Belgium]]. The current [[secretary-general]] is Jean-Christophe Kremer.<ref name="EPL">Food Drink Europe. "[http://www.fooddrinkeurope.eu/member/fedima/ FEDIMA – Federation of EU Manufacturers and Suppliers of Ingredients to the Bakery, Confectionery, and ''Patisserie'' Industries]". Accessed 22 Jan 2013.</ref> They sponsor annual symposia.<ref name="fer">[http://www.ferreconsulting.com Ferré & Consulting]. "[http://enblog.ferreconsulting.com/2012/02/25/fedima-about-ingredients-in-the-bakery-chain/ Fedima: about ingredients in the bakery chain]". 25 Feb 2012. Accessed 22 Jan 2013.</ref>
