{{Infobox person | name = Julie Fagerholt<!-- include middle initial, if not specified in birth_name --> | image = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1968|04|17}} | birth_place = [[Denmark]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|death date†|birth date†}} --> | death_place = | nationality = Danish | other_names = | occupation = Fashion designer | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works = }} '''Julie Fagerholt''' (born 17 April 1968) is a Danish fashion designer and founder of the luxury clothing brand Heartmade. She also creates ''[[haute couture]]''. Her customers include [[Crown Princess Mary of Denmark]].<ref name=cover>{{cite web|title=Chit-chat: Julie Fagerholt|url=http://cover.dk/blog/chit-chat-julie-fagerholt/|website=Cover|accessdate=2 March 2015|language=Danish}}</ref>
==Biography== Julie Fagerholt grew up in [[Skovshoved]] north of Copenhagen, the daughter of Ninja Tholstrup Bramsen, a child psychologist, and Nils Fagerholt, an architect and a professor at the [[Royal Danish Academy of Fine Arts]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.b.dk/kultur/prinsessen-i-pilestraede|title=Prinsessen fra Pilestræde|publisher=Berlingske|accessdate=29 January 2015|language=Danish}}</ref> She completed her education at the [[Danmarks Designskole|Danish Design School]] in 1993. In 1998, she set up her company Heartmade in a courtyard on [[Pilestræde]] in Copenhagen.
Originally focusing on ''haute couture'', the brand has mainly produced prét-à-porter collections since 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visitcopenhagen.dk/da/copenhagen/heartmade-gdk808018|title=Heartmade|publisher=Visit Denmark|accessdate=29 January 2015|language=Danish}}</ref> In 2000, her first collection won ''The Golden Button'',<ref name="danishfashioninstitute.dk">{{cite web|title=Julie Fagerholt Heartmade|url=http://danishfashioninstitute.dk/en/node/822|publisher=Danish Fashion Institute|accessdate=4 March 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151009212144/http://www.danishfashioninstitute.dk/en/node/822|archivedate=9 October 2015|df=}}</ref> a Danish fashion award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ciff.dk/news-julie-fagerholt-heartmade-exhibits-at-ciff.html|title=Julie Fagerholt Heartmade exhibits at CIFF|publisher=Copenhagen International Fashion Fair|accessdate=3 March 2015}}</ref> Her company has a flagship store at Pilestræde 45 in Copenhagen. Fagerholt ascribes some of her success to designing the kind of clothes she thinks she needs for herself but she is also inspired by ethnic clothing, for example from India.<ref name="cover" />
