'''King Shiloh''' is a [[roots reggae]] [[Sound system (DJ)|sound system]] from the Netherlands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://puglialive.net/home/news_det.php?nid=41870 |title=9 aprile - King Shiloh all'Arena Live Music di Carpignano Salentino (Lecce) |publisher=Puglialive |date=2001-04-09 |accessdate=2011-04-27|language=it}}</ref> According to their profile, they were "founded [...] through the inspiration of [[Rastafari movement|Jah Rastafari]]".
Their first album was released on [[Haile Selassie I of Ethiopia]]'s birthday, July 23, 1997.
As well as regularly ragging their enormous system at Amsterdam's DubClubY2K, King Shiloh have a show on the city's Radio 100 FM and occasionally appear in the UK.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spoonfed.co.uk/artist/dj-music-1425/king-shiloh-14884/ |title=King Shiloh, DJ Music, tickets and dates in London |publisher=Spoonfed.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2011-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110525112240/http://www.spoonfed.co.uk/artist/dj-music-1425/king-shiloh-14884/ |archivedate=2011-05-25 |df= }}</ref> They also play in other countries such as [[Germany]] or [[France]].
