{{Politics of Sri Lanka sidebar}}
The '''Primary Courts''' in [[Sri Lanka]] is a [[lower court]] and are the courts of first instance. There are seven Primary Courts, located in [[Anamaduwa]], [[Angunukolapelessa]], [[Kandy]], [[Mallakam]], [[Pilessa]], [[Wellawaya]] and [[Wennappuwa]]. In the other divisions, the [[Magistrate's Courts of Sri Lanka|Magistrate's Courts]] exercise the jurisdiction of the Primary Courts. The Primary Courts have criminal and civil Jurisdiction.<ref>[http://www.jsc.gov.lk/web/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=51&Itemid=64&lang=en Judicial Hierarchy]</ref> 

