'''Satelio''' is a [[pay-tv]] service for German-language television in [[Southern Africa]] (especially [[Namibia]] as well in [[South Africa]] (unter the [[Deukom]] label)), other African countries (Nigeria (since October 1, 2015)<ref name="nigeria">[http://www.satelio.tv/NI/index.html ''Satelio - vereinbart Vertriebspartnerschaft mit ACTV in Nigeria!.'' Satelio, 1. Oktober 2015] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003145629/http://www.satelio.tv/NI/index.html |date=2015-10-03 }}</ref>) and the [[Middle East]]. Satelio is provided by ''Deutscher Televisionsklub Betriebs GmbH'' based in [[Ismaning]], [[Germany]].
==Distribution== Satelio broadcast its offer via the [[Amos-5]] satellite (from 2 December 2013<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mantel|first1=Uwe|title=Satelio bringt deutsche Sender nach Afrika & Nahost|url=https://www.dwdl.de/nachrichten/43724/satelio_bringt_deutsche_sender_nach_afrika__nahost/|accessdate=7 November 2017|publisher=dwdl.de|date=2 December 2013}}</ref> to early June 2014 via [[Intelsat 20]]). Due to the failure of [[Amos-5]] on November 21, 2015,<ref>[http://www.satelio.tv/ ''Info Zeitpunkt 20:45 Uhr 21.Nov. 2015, AMOS-5 kann nicht mehr kontaktiert werden!.'' Satelio, 21. November 2015]</ref> the move to the [[Astra 4A]] satellite at [[Astra 5°E|5° east]] was announced on November 23, 2015<ref>[http://www.az.com.na/kommunikation/ein-neues-zuhause-im-all.428266 ''Ein neues Zuhause im All.'' Allgemeine Zeitung, 24. November 2015] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151124122823/http://www.az.com.na/kommunikation/ein-neues-zuhause-im-all.428266 |date=2015-11-24 }}</ref> and completed on November 24, 2015.
In Namibia, the broadcast takes place via the general broadcasting license of [[Hitradio Namibia]],<ref>[http://az.com.na/kommunikation/satelio-eine-fantastische-erg-nzung.414734 ''Satelio: Eine „fantastische Ergänzung“.'' Allgemeine Zeitung, 6. Dezember 2013] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211123810/http://az.com.na/kommunikation/satelio-eine-fantastische-erg-nzung.414734 |date=2013-12-11 }} abgerufen am 16. Januar 2014</ref> in Nigeria via ACTV.<ref name="nigeria"/>
