'''Science fiction and fantasy in the Serbia''' has a long and varied history.
== History == As far back as the end of the 18th century, [[science fiction]] elements can be found in [[Serbian literature]], but its modern period foundation is considered to commence with "Posle milijon godina" (After Million of Years), written by [[Dragutin Ilić]] in 1889, which is also considered the first [[science fiction]] theatrical play in the history of the [[world literature]]. [[Lazar Komarčić]]'s novel "Jedna ugašena zvezda" (An Extinct Star) followed, with publication in 1902.
Today, [[Zoran Živković (writer)]], winner of the [[World Fantasy Award]], is considered one of the best-known [[Serbians|Serbian]] [[science fiction]] authors, and perhaps the best known.
