'''Web4Dev''' is the name given a series of international conferences first convened in 2003 by the World Bank. Attendees, who include [[UN system]] organizations, international development agencies, international development [[NGO]]s and, on occasion, commercial partners, use the conferences to discuss how the internet related technologies can be applied to support the [[Millennium Development Goals]]. The community is now co-ordinated by UN System Chief Executives Board Secretariat.

The sixth annual conference was held in February 2010 in [[Brasilia]], under the oversight of [[UNESCO]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://portal.unesco.org/ci/en/ev.php-URL_ID=29506&URL_DO=DO_TOPIC&URL_SECTION=201.html|title=UNESCO Brasilia Office hosts sixth edition of Web4Dev conference|date=5 February 2010|accessdate=29 November 2011}}</ref>

